s to the Mayor and City Council on zoning, land use, and other planning issues\".<ref name=\"NPUs\">{{cite web|title=Neighborhood Planning Unit (NPU)|url=http://www.atlantaga.gov/index.aspx?page=739|website=City of Atlanta|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref> There are other non-official but widely recognized named areas within the city, such as [[Intown Atlanta|Intown]], [[West Midtown]], [[Buckhead]], and areas like Northwestern Atlanta identified by compass points.\n\n==Districts==\nThe term \"district\" in Atlanta is generally used for small areas within the official neighborhoods. [[Downtown Atlanta|Downtown]] and [[Midtown Atlanta|Midtown]] Atlanta each contain a number of districts. Another example is [[Little Five Points]], which sits on the border of 3 official neighborhoods.\n\nIn addition, Atlanta has various other divisions such as [[business improvement district]]s, [[Police Patrol Zones of Atlanta|police patrol zones]], and in the unique case of [[Buckhead (Atlanta)|Buckhead]], a \"community\". Most of Atlanta north of the [[I-75]] / [[I-85]] downtown connector is part of the \"Buckhead Community\".\n\n==Areas==\nAlthough all of Atlanta is officially divided into Neighborhood Planning Units, it is more common in the news media<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajc.com/news/atlanta-news/|title=Atlanta News / Georgia News Section|website=ajc|accessdate=28 August 2017}}</ref> to refer to the larger areas of the city in one of three ways:\n*Downtown, Midtown, and most of the central, east-central, west-central neighborhoods are referred to by their names, as these are well known throughout the Atlanta metro area, and most contain regional \"destinations\", such as the Zoo in Grant Park, or the shops and restaurants in Virginia Highland (other examples include East Lake, East Atlanta, Ormewood, Bankhead, Kirkwood, though they are not limited to these).\n*Buckhead neighborhoods are referred to collectively as Buckhead \u2013 this covers the entire northern fifth of the city (north of the I-75 / I-85 downtown connector)\n*Other areas are generally referred to as part of either \"Northwest\", \"Southwest\", or \"Southeast Atlanta\". However, \"East Atlanta\" refers to a small neighborhood which is part of the 'W' group NPU and does not have the same connotation as the other directional descriptors.\n<!-- Please do NOT include other cities or suburbs, ONLY areas within the city of Atlanta itself. -->\n\n==Neighborhoods (by area)==\nThe city of Atlanta lies in three [[counties in Georgia]]: primarily in [[Fulton County, Georgia|Fulton]], and partly in [[DeKalb County, Georgia|DeKalb]] to the east, and part [[Clayton County, Georgia|Clayton]] south of the county <br />''- Numbers to the right of the neighborhood indicate its position on the map above<br />- \"n\" is a link to the corresponding neighborhood association<br />- \"h\" indicates a link to the homepage of the corresponding historic district (if the neighborhood is one)''\n\n===Intown Atlanta===\nThe term \"intown\" is more commonly used to refer to any neighborhoods within the central part of the city.\n[[File:Neighborhoods of Intown Atlanta.jpg|thumb|900px|left|Neighborhoods of Intown Atlanta]]\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Downtown====\n*[[Downtown Atlanta]] [http://www.atlantadna.org n] is a neighborhood that contains the following sub-districts:\n**[[Castleberry Hill]] [http://www.castleberryhill.org n] [http://www.nps.gov/history/Nr/travel/atlanta/cas.htm h]\n**[[Centennial Hill]] district\n**[[Fairlie-Poplar]] district [http://www.nps.gov/history/Nr/travel/atlanta/fai.htm h]\n**[[Five Points (Atlanta)|Five Points]] district\n**[[Hotel District]] [http://www.nps.gov/history/Nr/travel/atlanta/hot.htm h]\n**[[Luckie Marietta]] district\n**[[Peachtree Center]]\n**[[SoNo (Atlanta)|SoNo]] [http://www.sonoatlanta.com n]\n**[[South Downtown]]\n{{col-break}}\n\n====Midtown====\n*[[Midtown Atlanta|Midtown]], as defined by the Midtown Alliance,<ref name=\"Midtown Alliance\">{{cite web|url=http://www.midtownatl.com/life/residential-neighborhoods/midtown-neighborhoods|title=Midtown Alliance|website=Midtownalliance.org|accessdate=30 August 2017}}</ref> consists of these neighborhoods:\n**The [[Midtown Atlanta|Midtown]]<!-- (7)--> neighborhood proper which contains the districts:\n***Midtown Core\n***Midtown Neighborhood [http://midtownatlanta.org/ n] [[Midtown Historic District (Atlanta, Georgia)|h]]\n**[[Ansley Park]] [http://www.ansleypark.org n]\n**[[Atlantic Station]]<!-- (16)--> [http://www.atlanticstation.com n]\n**[[Georgia Institute of Technology|Georgia Tech]] and [[Technology Square (Atlanta)|Technology Square]]\n**[[Home Park (Atlanta)|Home Park]] [http://www.homepark.org n]\n**[[Loring Heights (Atlanta)|Loring Heights]]\n**[[Sherwood Forest (Atlanta)|Sherwood Forest]]\n\n====West Midtown / Westside====\n*[[West Midtown]], a.k.a. Westside or The West Side, is an agglomeration of neighborhoods west of I-75/85 (frequently referred to as the \"Connector\") and is an unofficial area whose definition varies, and includes:\n**[[Berkeley Park]]\n**[[Blandtown]]\n** Western [[Home Park (Atlanta)|Home Park]]\n**[[Howell Station|Knight Park/Howell Station]]\n**[[Marietta Street Artery]]\nSometimes Bolton and Hills Park are also included (see below: [[Neighborhoods of Atlanta#Northwestern Atlanta|Northwestern Atlanta]])\n{{col-break}}\n\n{{anchor|East}}\n\n====East Side====\n*[[Atkins Park]]\n*[[Avondale Estates]]\n*[[Cabbagetown (Atlanta)|Cabbagetown]]\n*[[Candler Park]]\n*[[Druid Hills, Georgia|Druid Hills]] (part in Atlanta)\n*[[Decatur, Georgia|Decatur]]\n*[[East Atlanta]]\n*[[East Lake (Atlanta)|East Lake]]\n*[[Edgewood (Atlanta)|Edgewood]]\n*[[Inman Park]]\n*[[Kirkwood (Atlanta)|Kirkwood]]\n*[[Lake Claire (Atlanta)|Lake Claire]]\n*[[Lindridge-Martin Manor|Lindridge&#8209;Martin&nbsp;Manor]]\n*[[Morningside-Lenox Park|Morningside&#8209;Lenox&nbsp;Park]]\n*[[Oakland (Atlanta)|Oakland]]\n*[[Old Fourth Ward]]\n*[[Ormewood Park]]\n*[[Piedmont Heights (Atlanta)|Piedmont Heights]]\n*[[Poncey-Highland]]\n*[[Reynoldstown]]\n*[[Sweet Auburn]]\n*[[Scottdale, Georgia|Scottdale]]\n*[[Virginia-Highland]]\n{{col-break}}\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n{{col-end}}\nThe [[Little Five Points]] district is located where [[Inman Park]] and [[Candler Park]] meet.\n\n===Southeastern Atlanta===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n*Amal Heights\n*[[Benteen Park]]\n*Betmar LaVilla\n*Blair Villa/Poole Creek\n*Boulevard Heights\n*Browns Mill Park\n*[[Chosewood Park]]\n*Custer/McDonough/Guice\n*Englewood Manor ([[Atlanta Housing Authority|AHA]] property demolished 2008)\n*Glenrose Heights\n*[[Grant Park (Atlanta)|Grant Park]]\n*[[High Point (Atlanta)|High Point]]\n*[[Joyland (Atlanta)|Joyland]]\n*Lakewood\n*[[Lakewood Heights (Atlanta)|Lakewood Heights]]\n{{col-break}}\n*Leila Valley ([[Atlanta Housing Authority|AHA]] property demolished 2008)\n*Norwood Manor\n*Orchard Knob\n*[[Peoplestown]]\n*Polar Rock\n*Rebel Valley Forest\n*Rosedale Heights\n*[[South Atlanta]]\n*South River Gardens\n*State Facility\n*[[Summerhill (Atlanta)|Summerhill]]\n*Swallow Circle/Baywood\n*[[Atlanta mixed-income communities#The Villages at Carver|The Villages at Carver]]\n*Thomasville Heights\u2014 not to be confused with the [[Demolished public housing projects in Atlanta#Thomasville Heights|former housing project of the same name]], located near the neighborhood. ([[Atlanta Housing Authority|AHA]] property demolished 2010\u201311)\n*Woodland Hills\n{{col-break}}\n[[File:Neighborhoods of Southeast Atlanta.jpg|thumb|350px|right|Neighborhoods of Southeast Atlanta]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Southwestern Atlanta===\n{{See also|SWATS}}\n[[File:Neighborhoods of Southwest Atlanta.jpg|thumb|left|900px|Southwest Atlanta]]\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n*Adams Park\n*[[Adamsville (Atlanta)|Adamsville]]\n*Arlington Estates\n*[[Ashley Collegetown]] (former [[Demolished public housing projects in Atlanta#Harris Chiles|Harris Chiles]])\n*[[Atlanta mixed-income communities#Ashley Courts at Cascade|Ashley Courts]]\n*[[Ashview Heights]]\n*[[Atlanta University Center]]\n*Audubon Forest\n*Audubon Forest West\n*Baker Hills\n*Bakers Ferry\n*Beecher Hills\n*[[Ben Hill (Atlanta)|Ben Hill]]\n*Ben Hill Acres\n*Ben Hill Forest\n*Ben Hill Pines\n*Ben Hill Terrace\n*Boulder Park\n*Brentwood\n*Briar Glen\n*Bush Mountain\n*Butner/Tell\n*Campbellton Road\n{{col-break}}\n*[[Capitol View (Atlanta)|Capitol View]]\n*[[Capitol View Manor]]\n*Carroll Heights\n*Cascade Avenue/Road\n*Cascade Green\n*[[Cascade Heights]]\n*Chalet Woods\n*[[Collier Heights]]\n*Deerwood\n*East Ardley Road\n*Elmco Estates\n*Fairburn\n*Fairburn Heights\n*Fairburn Road/Wisteria Lane\n*Fairburn Tell\n*Fairburn Mays\n*Fairway Acres\n*Florida Heights\n*[[Fort McPherson]]\n*Fort Valley\n*Green Acres Valley\n*Green Forest Acres\n*[[Greenbriar (Atlanta)|Greenbriar]]\n*Greenbriar Village\n{{col-break}}\n*Hammond Park\n*Harland Terrace\n*Heritage Valley\n*Horseshoe Community\n*[[Hunter Hills]]\n*Huntington\n*Ivan Hill\n*[[Just Us (Atlanta)|Just Us]]\n*Kings Forest\n*Lake Estates\n*Laurens Valley\n*Magnum Manor\n*Mays\n*Meadowbrook Forest\n*[[Mechanicsville (Atlanta)|Mechanicsville]]\n*Mellwood\n*[[Midwest Cascade]]\n*Mt. Gilead Woods\n*Niskey Cove\n*[[Niskey Lake]]\n*Oakcliff\n*[[Oakland City (Atlanta)|Oakland City]]\n*Old Fairburn Village\n*Old Gordon\n{{col-break}}\n*Pomona Park\n*[[Perkerson (Atlanta)|Perkerson]]\n*Peyton Forest\n*[[Pittsburgh (Atlanta)|Pittsburgh]]\n*Princeton Lakes\n*Regency Trace\n*Ridgecrest Forest\n*Rue Royal\n*Sandlewood Estates\n*South Oaks\n*Southwest\n*[[Summerdale Commons]]\n*[[Sylvan Hills (Atlanta)|Sylvan Hills]]\n*Tampa Park\n*[[Venetian Hills]]\n*[[West End (Atlanta)|West End]]\n*West Manor\n*Westhaven\n*[[Westview (Atlanta)|Westview]]\n*Westwood Terrace\n*Wildwood\n*Wildwood Forest\n*Wilson Mill Meadows\n*Wisteria Gardens\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Northwestern Atlanta===\n[[File:Neighborhoods of Northwest Atlanta.jpg|thumb|left|900px|Northwest Atlanta]]\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n*Almond Park\n*Atlanta Industrial Park\n*[[Bankhead (Atlanta)|Bankhead]]\n*[[Bankhead Courts]] ([[Atlanta Housing Authority|AHA]] property demolished 2010)\n*[[Bolton (Atlanta)|Bolton]]\n*Bolton Hills\n*[[Bowen Apartments]]\n{{col-break}}\n*Brookview Heights\n*Carey Park\n*Carver Hills\n*[[Center Hill (Atlanta)|Center Hill]]\n*Chattahoochee\n*[[Dixie Hills, Atlanta|Dixie Hills]]\n*[[English Avenue (Atlanta)|English Avenue]]\n*English Park\n*[[Grove Park (Atlanta)|Grove Park]]\n{{col-break}}\n*Harvel Homes\n*Hills Park\n*[[Hunter Hills]]\n*[[Knight Park-Howell Station|Knight Park/Howell Station]]\n*Monroe Heights(45)\n*[[Mozley Park]]\n*Penelope Neighbors\n*[[Riverside (Atlanta)|Riverside]]\n{{col-break}}\n*Rockdale\n*Scotts Crossing\n*[[Vine City]]\n*[[Washington Park (Atlanta, Georgia)|Washington Park]]\n*[[Atlanta mixed-income communities#West Highlands|West Highlands]] (includes Perry Homes)\n*[[West Lake (MARTA station)|West Lake]]\n*[[Whittier Mill Village]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Buckhead===\n[[File:Neighborhoods of Buckhead.jpg|thumb|left|900px|Buckhead]]\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-break}}\n*[[Ardmore (Atlanta)|Ardmore]]\n*[[Argonne Forest (Atlanta)|Argonne Forest]]\n*Arden/Habersham\n*[[Brookhaven (Atlanta)|Brookhaven]]\n*[[Buckhead Forest]]\n*Brandon\n*[[Brookwood (Atlanta)|Brookwood]]\n*[[Brookwood Hills]]\n*[[Buckhead Forest]]\n*[[Buckhead Village]]\n*Castlewood\n*Channing Valley (also includes Memorial Park)\n{{col-break}}\n*[[Chastain Park]]\n*[[Collier Hills]] (also includes [[Brookwood Hills]])\n*Colonial Homes\n*East Chastain Park\n*[[Garden Hills]]\n*Haynes Manor\n*[[Historic Brookhaven (Atlanta)|Historic Brookhaven]]\n*Kingswood\n*[[Lindbergh/Morosgo]]\n*[[Loring Heights (Atlanta)|Loring Heights]]\n*[[Margaret Mitchell (Atlanta neighborhood)|Margaret Mitchell]]\n*Mount Paran/Northside\n{{col-break}}\n*Mount Paran Parkway\n*[[North Buckhead]]\n*[[Paces (Atlanta)|Paces]]\n*Peachtree Heights East\n*Peachtree Heights West\n*