{"title_page": "Anthony Errington", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}\n\n'''Anthony Errington''', [[D.D.]] (died 1719?), was an English Catholic [[Anglicanism#Anglican divines|divine]].\n\nErrington was a member of a [[Northumbria]]n family. His name appears on a list of writers at the English College, [[Douai]], but he was more probably educated at Lisbon and Paris. He is said to have died about 1719.\n\nHe wrote:\n* \u2018Catechistical Discourses,\u2019 Paris, 1654, 16mo, dedicated to the \u2018[[Henrietta Maria of France|Princesse Henrietta Maria]], daughter of England.\u2019\n* \u2018Missionarium: sive opusculum practicum, pro fide propaganda et conservanda,\u2019 Rome, 1672, 12mo.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{DNB|wstitle=Errington, Anthony}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Errington, Anthony}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:1719 deaths]]\n[[Category:English Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:18th-century Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:18th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:18th-century male writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}\n\n'''Anthony Errington''', [[D.D.]] (died 1719?), was an English Catholic [[Anglicanism#Anglican divines|divine]].\n\nErrington was a member of a [[Northumbria]]n family. His name appears on a list of writers at the English College, [[Douai]], but he was more probably educated at Lisbon and Paris. He is said to have died about 1719.\n\nHe wrote:\n* \u2018Catechistical Discourses,\u2019 Paris, 1654, 16mo, dedicated to the \u2018[[Henrietta Maria of France|Princesse Henrietta Maria]], daughter of England.\u2019\n* \u2018Missionarium: sive opusculum practicum, pro fide propaganda et conservanda,\u2019 Rome, 1672, 12mo.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{DNB|wstitle=Errington, Anthony}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Errington, Anthony}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:1719 deaths]]\n[[Category:English Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:18th-century Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:18th-century English writers]]\n[[Category:18th-century male writers]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Errington"}
