proper capabilities to restore the fort is the [[National Museum of the Philippines]].<ref>http://www.localphilippines.com/attractions/kuta</ref>\n\n==Barangays==\n\nBongabong is politically subdivided into 36 [[barangay]]s.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! Barangay\n! Population (2016)\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Anilao\n| 2,956\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Batangan\n| 1,279\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Bukal\n| 783\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Camantigue\n| 1,782\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Carmundo\n| 1,649\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Cawayan\n| 2,957\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Dayhagan\n| 1,990\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Formon\n| 1,587\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Hagan\n| 3,397\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Hagupit\n| 672\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Kaligtasan\n| 2,467\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Labasan\n| 4,713\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Labonan\n| 1,562\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Libertad\n| 1,736\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Lisap\n| 6,075\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Luna\n| 1,293\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Malitbog\n| 3,131\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Mapang\n| 825\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Masaguisi\n| 2,257\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Morente\n| 1,833\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Ogbot\n| 1,171\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Orconuma\n| 1,860\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Polusahi\n| 1,011\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Sagana\n| 2,699\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| San Isidro\n| 2,082\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| San Jose\n| 1,115\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| San Juan\n| 467\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Santa Cruz\n| 1,215\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Sigange\n| 1,348\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Tawas\n| 1,485\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Poblacion\n| 1,790\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Aplaya\n| 2,702\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Bagumbayan I\n| 2,323\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Bagumbayan II\n| 1,465\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Ipil\n| 2,589\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| Mina de Oro\n| 1,807\n|-\n! Total\n! 72,073\n|}\n\n<!-- ==History==\n\n{{Empty section|date=July 2010}}\n\n==Economy==\n\n{{Empty section|date=July 2010}}\n-->\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Philippine Census \n| al